Mario Masla&lt;U+0107&gt; (Serbian Cyrillic: Map&lt;U+0438&gt;o Mac&lt;U+043B&gt;a&lt;U+045B&gt;, born 9 September 1990 in Novi Sad) is a Serbian football defender playing with FK Borac &lt;U+010C&gt;a&lt;U+010D&gt;ak in the Serbian SuperLiga.
He made his senior debut in the season 2008-09 with FK Veternik before moving in summer 2009 to FK Borac &lt;U+010C&gt;a&lt;U+010D&gt;ak.1 He plays as central defender.
He is member of the Serbia national under-21 football team.2
